The paper discusses an integrated framework for benchmarking compute-in-memory (CIM) accelerators for deep neural networks, with hierarchical design options from device-level to algorithm-level. This work involves the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science, including computer architecture (cs.AR), emerging technologies (cs.ET), neural networks (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and electronics (cs.EM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
